<subSubSection pageId="134" pageNumber="135" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="134" pageNumber="135">
Although described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brocchii Michelotti" authorityYear="1847" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melania" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melania" order="Pteropoda" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Melania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not considered a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H.Adams &amp; A.Adams" authorityYear="1854" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Not" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Melanopsidae</taxonomicName>
today, this species is included and briefly discussed here because it has been repeatedly considered a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. B. L. d'A. de Ferussac in J. B. L. d'A. de Ferussac &amp; A. E. J. P. J. F. d'A. de Ferussac" authorityYear="1807" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melanopsis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanopsis" order="Pteropoda" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Melanopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimens had been apparently sent to Von dem Busch or Philippi by Meder, who had named the species &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. B. L. d'A. de Ferussac in J. B. L. d'A. de Ferussac &amp; A. E. J. P. J. F. d'A. de Ferussac" authorityYear="1807" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melanopsis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanopsis" order="Pteropoda" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Melanopsis</taxonomicName>
Helena
</emphasis>
&quot;. The description, however, stems clearly from Von dem Busch. The species epithet is a noun in apposition and needs not to agree in gender with the generic name (Art. 31.2.1). Currently considered to belong in the marine genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H.Adams &amp; A.Adams" authorityYear="1855" class="Gastropoda" family="Nassariidae" genus="Clea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Clea" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Clea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
H. Adams &amp; A. Adams, 1855 (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" class="Gastropoda" family="Buccinidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Sorbeoconcha" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Buccinidae</taxonomicName>
) (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Coelho, AR" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Aquaculture &amp; Research Development" pageId="305" pageNumber="306" publicationUrl="10.4172/2155-9546.1000187" refId="B91" refString="Coelho, AR, Dinis, MT, Reis, J, 2013. Effect of Diet and Stocking Densities on Life History Traits of Clea helena (Philippi 1847) Reared in Captivity. Journal of Aquaculture &amp; Research Development 4 (5), DOI: 10.4172/2155-9546.1000187" title="Effect of Diet and Stocking Densities on Life History Traits of Clea helena (Philippi 1847) Reared in Captivity." url="10.4172/2155-9546.1000187" volume="4" year="2013">Coelho et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
